-- MOVES- CaixaBank, BofA, AON Hewitt, AXA Investment Managers
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 04:05PM EDT
-- None



June 30 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Monday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

CAIXABANK <CABK.MC> The Spanish bank said on Monday it would replace Chief Executive Juan Maria Nin with Chief Financial Officer Gonzalo Gortazar. Gortazar, 48, has held senior positions at La Caixa for the last five years and previously worked for Morgan Stanley and Bank of America. [ID:nL6N0PB4OI]  BANK OF AMERICA <BAC.N> The bank named Jeremy Murphy managing director in its Americas consumer and retail investment banking group, it said in an internal memo seen by Reuters. The appointment was confirmed by a Bank of America spokesman. Murphy, who will be based in New York, will join the bank in fall.  He joins from Barclays <BARC.L>, where he was managing director of consumer and retail investment banking group, focused on the food sector. [ID:nL4N0PB3WE]  AON HEWITT Aon Plc's <AON.N> management consulting business appointed Dave Lyons as a principal consultant at its global investment practice business. Lyons joins Aon Hewitt from Deloitte, where he was head of research and led its public sector investment consulting business. He had also worked at JLT. [ID:nL4N0PB2MG]  AXA INVESTMENT MANAGERS  The asset management arm of AXA Group <AXAF.PA> appointed Daoyu Chen as portfolio manager at its liability driven investments team for UK pension schemes. Daoyu joins AXA IM from Goldman Sachs Group <GS.N>, where she traded Sterling interest rate swaps and cross currency swaps. [ID:nL4N0PB374]  PERELLA WEINBERG PARTNERS The asset management services company appointed Jorma Ollila as an advisory partner. Ollila is currently chairman of the board at Royal Dutch Shell Plc <RDSa.L> and Outokumpu Oyj <OUT1V.HE>. He was earlier chief executive officer of Nokia <NOK1V.HE>.